<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Basic HTML Page</title>
    <style>
        /* This is an internal CSS stylesheet */
        
        /* Style for the whole page body */
        body {
            background-color: #f0f8ff; /* A light aliceblue background color */
        }
        
        /* Style for the main heading */
        h1 {
            color: #000080; /* A navy blue text color */
        }

        /* New card class */
        .card {
            background-color: white;
            border: 1px solid #dddddd; /* Adds a light grey border */
            padding: 20px;              /* Adds space inside the card */
            box-shadow: 2px 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); /* Adds a subtle shadow */
            margin-top: 20px;           /* Adds space above the card */
            margin-bottom: 20px;        /* Adds space below the card */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Welcome to My Web Page</h1>
    
    <p>This is a simple paragraph demonstrating a basic HTML structure. You can replace this text with your own content. HTML is the standard markup language for creating web pages and web applications.</p>
    
    <img 
        src="https://placehold.co/600x400/3498db/ffffff?text=My+Awesome+Image"
        alt="A placeholder image"
    >

    <!-- New div with the .card class applied -->
    <div class="card">
        <h3>This is a Card</h3>
        <p>This div has a border, padding, and a shadow applied using our new CSS class.</p>
    </div>
    
    <hr>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    
    <form>
        <label for="name">Name:</label><br>
        <input type="text" id="name" name="name"><br><br>
        
        <label for="email">Email:</label><br>
        <input type="email" id="email" name="email"><br><br>
        
        <input type="submit" value="Submit">
    </form>
        
</body>
</html>
